OL,3,C'It couldn't come soon enough.' Baby
OL,4,Closs certificates offered to more
OL,5,Cparents
OL,7,FA mother from Warwickshire has spoken
OL,8,Fof her relief at being able to
OL,9,Fofficially recognise the loss of her
OL,10,Fbaby in early pregnancy.
OL,12,FRebekah Stocker and her husband James
OL,13,Ffrom Coleshill were told at their 12
OL,14,Fweek scan that they had lost their
OL,15,Fbaby who they had named Joa.
OL,17,FThe lack of an official certificate or
OL,18,Fany recognition that they'd been
OL,19,Fexpecting a child, was difficult to
OL,20,Fbear.
